race.description: Sportsbet Viddora Series Final F&M Handicap
race.comment: One of the races of the day with the market suggesting there isn't much between several of these handy mares. MYSTIC WONDER (1) is on the seven-day back-up after going under as a well-supported favourite last week. She has to contend with the big weight again but she will appreciate getting back to the main track at Morphettville. She can roll forward and, with the benefit of a couple of runs under her belt, take some catching. ANGEL TORQUE (4) is another that can be forgiven for a last start defeat. Her prior win was super and she maps to get the perfect run from barrier three here. She's a definite danger. Giving strong consideration to the Stokes pair of MISLUDI (11) and STOLEN KISS (10). MISLUDI will likely concede a start but will be finishing into the money, while STOLEN KISS doesn't win out of turn but rarely runs poorly. Throw in ALL TOO MYSTI (9) in exotics and quaddies.
